e\"><span class=\"linenumber\">7</span><span data-text=\"θηγανείτα\" data-n=\"100\" data-lemma=\"\">θηγανείτα</span>  <span data-text=\"ἀπὸ\" data-n=\"105\" data-lemma=\"\">ἀπὸ</span>  <span data-text=\"τᾶς\" data-n=\"110\" data-lemma=\"\">τᾶς</span>  <br id=\"al8-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">8</span><span data-text=\"πύλας\" data-n=\"115\" data-lemma=\"\">[π]ύλας</span>  <span data-text=\"τᾶς\" data-n=\"120\" data-lemma=\"\">τᾶς</span>  <span data-text=\"παρὰ\" data-n=\"125\" data-lemma=\"\">παρὰ</span>  <br id=\"al9-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">9</span><span data-text=\"θάλασσαν\" data-n=\"130\" data-lemma=\"\">θ̣άλασσαν</span>  <span data-text=\"ἐκ\" data-n=\"135\" data-lemma=\"\">ἐκ</span>  <span data-text=\"τοῦ\" data-n=\"140\" data-lemma=\"\">τοῦ</span>  <span data-text=\"ἰδίου\" data-n=\"145\" data-lemma=\"\">ἰδίο[υ]</span>  <br id=\"al10-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">10</span><span data-text=\"ποιήσαντα\" data-n=\"150\" data-lemma=\"\">[π]ο̣ι̣ήσαντα</span>  <span dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)</span><span data-text=\"εὐνοίας\" data-n=\"160\" data-lemma=\"\">εὐνοίας</span>  <br id=\"al11-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">11</span><span data-text=\"ἕνεκα\" data-n=\"165\" data-lemma=\"\">[ἕνεκα]</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">⁦ - - - - - - - - - - ⁩</span>]<br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"ἐπὶ τὸ\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"\">[.]....Ο</span><span data-text=\"άλειπτήριον\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"\">ΑΛΕΙ.[......</span><span data-text=\"ἐκ\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"\">..</span><span data-text=\"τοῦ\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"\">...]</span><br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"ἰδίου\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"\">[.]ΔΙΟΥ</span><span data-text=\"ποιήσαντα\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"\">ΠΟΙΗ.....</span><br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"καὶ\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"\">[.]ΑΙ</span><span data-text=\"τὰς\" data-n=\"45\" data-lemma=\"\">ΤΑΣ</span><span data-text=\"διώρυγας\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"\">ΔΙΩΡΥΓΑΣ</span><span data-text=\"καὶ τὰν\" data-n=\"55\" data-lemma=\"\">.....[..]</span><br id=\"al5-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span><span data-text=\"στρῶσιν\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"\">[.]ΤΡΩΣΙΝ</span><span data-text=\"τᾶς\" data-n=\"65\" data-lemma=\"\">ΤΑΣ</span><span data-text=\"πλατείας\" data-n=\"70\" data-lemma=\"\">ΠΛΑΤΕΙΑΣ</span><span data-text=\"τὰν\" data-n=\"75\" data-lemma=\"\">ΤΑ[.]</span><br id=\"al6-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">6</span><span data-text=\"ἀπὸ\" data-n=\"80\" data-lemma=\"\">[.]ΠΟ</span><span data-text=\"τοῦ\" data-n=\"85\" data-lemma=\"\">ΤΟΥ</span><span data-text=\"λίθου\" data-n=\"90\" data-lemma=\"\">ΛΙΘΟΥ</span><span data-text=\"τοῦ\" data-n=\"95\" data-lemma=\"\">ΤΟΥ</span><br id=\"al7-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">7</span><span data-text=\"θηγανείτα\" data-n=\"100\" data-lemma=\"\">ΘΗΓΑΝΕΙΤΑ</span><span data-text=\"ἀπὸ\" data-n=\"105\" data-lemma=\"\">ΑΠΟ</span><span data-text=\"τᾶς\" data-n=\"110\" data-lemma=\"\">ΤΑΣ</span><br id=\"al8-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">8</span><span data-text=\"πύλας\" data-n=\"115\" data-lemma=\"\">[.]ΥΛΑΣ</span><span data-text=\"τᾶς\" data-n=\"120\" data-lemma=\"\">ΤΑΣ</span><span data-text=\"παρὰ\" data-n=\"125\" data-lemma=\"\">ΠΑΡΑ</span><br id=\"al9-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">9</span><span data-text=\"θάλασσαν\" data-n=\"130\" data-lemma=\"\">.ΑΛΑΣΣΑΝ</span><span data-text=\"ἐκ\" data-n=\"135\" data-lemma=\"\">ΕΚ</span><span data-text=\"τοῦ\" data-n=\"140\" data-lemma=\"\">ΤΟΥ</span><span data-text=\"ἰδίου\" data-n=\"145\" data-lemma=\"\">ΙΔΙΟ[.]</span><br id=\"al10-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">10</span><span data-text=\"ποιήσαντα\" data-n=\"150\" data-lemma=\"\">[.]..ΗΣΑΝΤΑ</span> &nbsp;&nbsp; <span data-text=\"εὐνοίας\" data-n=\"160\" data-lemma=\"\">ΕΥΝΟΙΑΣ</span><br id=\"al11-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">11</span><span data-text=\"ἕνεκα\" data-n=\"165\" data-lemma=\"\">[.....]</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic001136_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo civico di Termini Imerese\" src=\"ISic001136_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001136.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo civico di Termini Imerese\" src=\"ISic001136-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic001136_leftthreequarter_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo civico di Termini Imerese\" src=\"ISic001136_leftthreequarter_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001136_leftthreequarter.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo civico di Termini Imerese\" src=\"ISic001136_leftthreequarter-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text from autopsy</span>  </span>; </li><li><span class=\"1\">1: <span>the traces appear compatible with ΣΙΑ or ΣΙΛ (so Mauceri also); Salinas notes two traces</span>  </span><br></li><li><span class=\"2\">2: <span>Gualtherus: .ΙΟΛΛΕΙ...; Salinas: ΙΟΛΛΕΙ.; Mauceri: _ΟΟΑΛΕΙ</span>  </span><br></li><li><span class=\"3\">3: <span>Gualtherus: .ΛΙΟΥΠΟ...ΠΙΣΑΙ...; Salinas: ΔΙΟΥΠΟΙΗΣ</span>  </span><br></li><li><span class=\"7\">7: <span>Gualtherus: ΑΠΟΤΤΑΣ</span>  </span><br></li><li><span class=\"11\">11: <span>Kaibel and Salinas (NSA) read a single vertical beneath the first alpha of line 10; Kaibel: [χάριν]; Bechtel: [ἕνε]κ[α]; Salinas et ceteri: [ἕνεκα].</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>[...name of individual...] undertook the paving and the conduits of the main street at his own expense using whetstone, from the maritime gate up to the aleipterion. (Erected) for the sake of good will.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Kaibel proposed 'alexandreion' in line 2 with the comment 'sumpsi to alexandreion fuisse aedificium publicum, velut gymnasium', with implied parallels such as Netum's Hieroneion and Syracuse's Timoleionteion. The other proposed restoration, adopted by Dubois, Brugnone, et al., is 'aleipterion', a 'place for anointing' in a gymnasium, used also as sudatory. The inscription must record honours for someone who saw to the paving and drainage of the main street between this building and the maritime gates, with stone described by a hapax in Doric form, which seems to signify stone used for sharpening (a whet stone) and so a particularly hard and durable stone. The name of the individual is lost, perhaps originally at the top of the text in the accusative. It is quite possible that another line is lost from above the traces in line 1. The end of the text is also lost, but there is clearly a vacat on the lower right, suggesting only a single word is missing at the start of line 11. Salinas observed a vertical, and traces are visible below the alpha above of what appears to be a Ν. Sicilian honorifics of the Hellenistic period very commonly end εὐνοίας ἕνεκεν (rather than ἕνεκα), and the traces are compatible with the end of ἕνεκεν (albeit slightly squeezed compared to the line above). Given the trace, Kaibel's suggestion of χάριν is the other plausible alternative, but this is not typically found in Sicilian texts of this sort.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 3247 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817</a>  </li><li> Gualtherus 1624 no. 82 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388</a>  </li><li> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] no.240 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931</a>  </li><li> Castelli 1784 284 cl.18, no.24 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083</a>  </li><li> Franz 1853 5578 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250</a>  </li><li> Mauceri 1878 168-169 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10003135\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10003135</a>  </li><li> Salinas NSA 1878 72 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392</a>  </li><li> Kaibel 1890 <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">317</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a>  </li><li> Brugnone 1974 2 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001397\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001397</a>  </li><li> Dubois 1989 <a href=\"http://www.persee.fr/doc/efr_0000-0000_1989_cat_119_1\" target=\"_blank\">202</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000187\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000187</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Regularly cut letters with terminal serifs including horizontal caps to the tops of the alphas. Alpha has generally curved crossbar, sometimes equivalent to broken bar; epsilon has detached middle bar in the form of a triangle; theta has central point; kappa has full-length arms; omicron is full-size; pi has equal length verticals and overlapping horizontal; rho has a tapering eye; sigma has horizontal top and bottom, which overextend to left, the mid-strokes extending halfway, and straight; upsilon has straight arms; omega is tear-drop shaped, and closed, on a horizontal line.</p> <p> Types list: <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.4.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.4</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.5.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.5</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Θ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Θ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Θ-type1.4.html\" target=\"_blank\">Θ type1.4</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ο-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ο type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-tyoe3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ tyoe3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2.2.1</a> </p> Line 1  incomplete  Line 2  24-27  Line 3  28-30  Line 4  23-30  Line 5  25-30  Line 6  25-29  Line 7  26-31  Line 8  25-30  Line 9  25-29  Line 10  27-30  Interlineation line 1 to 10  7-10  </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
